'''Soul Blazer''' was developed by '''Quintet''' and published by '''Enix''' in 1992. This page documents the development team, credits, and historical context.

== Development Team ==

=== Quintet Corporation ===
Quintet was a Japanese video game developer founded in 1989 by former Nihon Falcom employees. They specialized in action RPGs and were known for their "Soul trilogy" (Soul Blazer, Illusion of Gaia, Terranigma) published by Enix.

