== Legacy ==

=== Spiritual Successors ===

Soul Blazer was the first in what fans call the "Soul Trilogy":

# '''Soul Blazer''' (1992) - The original
# '''Illusion of Gaia''' (1993) - More action-focused
# '''Terranigma''' (1995) - Final and most ambitious

All three games share:
* Creation/resurrection themes
* Action RPG gameplay
* Quintet development team
* Enix publishing

=== Modern Availability ===

As of 2024, Soul Blazer has not been officially re-released on any modern platform. Options for playing:
* Original SNES cartridge
* SNES Classic (via modding)
* Emulation

== Development Trivia ==

* Soul Blazer was originally conceived as a sequel to ActRaiser
* The game engine was heavily modified from ActRaiser
* Development took approximately 18 months
* The team was approximately 15 people
* Sound was composed on actual SNES hardware
* Debug mode code remains in US ROM (Game Genie enabled)

